        "title": "feat: add scoped mention pattern policy",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a shared scoped mention-pattern policy for global, agent, and provider/channel overrides\n- apply configured mention-pattern gating across channel runtimes while preserving native mentions\n- document raw regex-body syntax and regenerate config/help metadata\n\n## Notes\n- Recreated from a clean `origin/main` branch after #70846 was closed as dirty; this branch has been rebased on current `origin/main` and generated baselines refreshed after upstream movement.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm --config.minimum-release-age=0 install --lockfile-only --ignore-scripts=false --config.engine-strict=false --config.enable-pre-post-scripts=true --config.side-effects-cache=true`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- `pnpm config:docs:check`\n- `pnpm test extensions/qa-channel/src/inbound.test.ts src/channels/mention-pattern-policy.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nCurrent head: `103a1fbd3d` (`103a1fbd3d5f4db39dd847298ffa05d2ba2b33df`).\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Scoped mention-pattern policy for Telegram forum-topic media pre-download gating, plus current CI guard regressions for shrinkwrap check context and Azure Speech env-restore security scanning.\n- **Real environment tested:** PR checkout on Patrick's OpenClaw workspace using Node 24.13.0 / npm 11.6.2 for shrinkwrap parity, and the repository's real Telegram mention-policy proof harness against the changed runtime sources.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** `HEAD_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD); HEAD_SHORT=$(git rev-parse --short=10 HEAD); HEAD_SHA=$HEAD_SHA HEAD_SHORT=$HEAD_SHORT node --import tsx /tmp/pr70864-proof-c770334.mjs`\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the exact current head:\n\n```text\nOpenClaw scoped mention policy Telegram media pre-download proof (103a1fbd3d, 103a1fbd3d5f4db39dd847298ffa05d2ba2b33df)\n{\"topic